HEADWORD: pasta
<hw>pas"ta</hw> <pr>(p⟦adot⟧"st⟦adot⟧; Brit. p⟦acr⟧s"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of a variety of edible unleavened doughey
preparations made from flour, eggs and water, originating in
<country>Italy</country>, and shaped into various forms, such as solid
strings (as spaghetti), hollow tubes, or layered squares (ravioli). They
may be mixed with various sauces, often having a tomato base, or filled
with meat or cheese fillings.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Italian paste, paste.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paste</ent>⟦br⟧
